@jorisvandenbossche Thanks for the review!

> It would be great if you could also write some narrative with the indexing rules that follow your new added tests.

What exactly do you mean? Where would I add this narrative?

@zfrenchee I may have some time to do this in a few weeks. A few important caveats. Having tests that are self-consistent is the most important thing here. Please mark tests (via comment is fine), on ones where this is the correct way, with no ambiguity and there is one obvious answer.

Any tests which are in any way subjective should be segregated to separate tests, and marked this way.

What happes with an implementation is that you make the most important / most correct things work first. Having tests that we are still discussing makes things very confusing.

@jreback Would you please elaborate on 

> Please mark tests (via comment is fine), on ones where this is the correct way, with no ambiguity and there is one obvious answer.

I'm not sure I understand.
